I agree with Didi the OT gets so boring at times, the last time I was there we had a really good Cleric, a great Monk, and one of my favorite Warriors that I rarely get to play, and after a half hour of the usual pulling I was joking with him about being a boring puller because he was only bring 4 or 5 mobs at a time, so he gave me a challenge and pulled over ten mobs at once, wow did that make me work my robe off, but we did it and none of us died, so we kept it up for awhile and everytime he would up the ante a little more, I love stuff like that it really shows me what a Enchanter can do, big out door zones for huge CC, but the dungeons is where it is at.<br>
Doing SolB and Drogas is a thrill ride, SolB is wild evreything is so close together and the adds are insane, Drogas is great because you really need a Enchanter to get through the place<br>
if your group is under 40 in levels.<br>
I have played a Ranger on of FV and tried almost all the other classes out on other servers (but none over 20, even tried a few on a Zek) and Enchanters are my favorite by far, great for RP, needed at higher levels, needed at lower levels though most do not know it, but when you are in CB or EC fighting orcs and the adds show up your Cleric will love haveing a Enchanter around not just for breeze, but for mana saved not having to heal everyone because they are getting beat by five mobs at once.<br>
The biggest challenge for me being a Enchanter is dueling, I have to learn everything about all the classes, their weakness and more importantly their strengths, we are horrible at DD and DoT, our pets are not tanks and cannot take alot of damage, but what I have found is that we can be impressive in duels the same as in groups by manipulating our targets, <br>
I have had impressive wins over some that are way higher than me in seasons as well as being owned by those ten levels younger than I, but I will admit I lose way more than I win, as with everything it is all about gear, knowledge and stratagy, I have heard accounts of Enchanters winning best of the best competitions on other servers in arenas (meaning no mobs to charm, just spells and animations) so there is hope for us in the end. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xtailia>Xtailia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/1/03 6:14:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=119.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Frances</span><hr size=1> *laugh* I think at one time every enchanter has complained about boring pulls, and every puller has taken it as a challenge to see how big a pull they can bring.  I think enchanters are an absolutely great class..  I have not had the urge to level quickly because it is a completely different game than a rogue.<br>
<br>
Enchangers are also quite unique in that the roll of soloing is identical to the role of grouping, assuming charm solo and typical group makeup.  The enchanter sits back watching the fight, and reacts when things go bad.  Therefore a soloing enchanter isn't neglecting grouping skills so much.<br>
<br>
An enchanter pretty much always has to have at least some control over the group.  Their role is all about control, if an enchanter has no control they aren't really doing anything. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44>Tower of Magick</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.240<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

